1
00:00:09,583 --> 00:00:12,500
[CHIHIRO]
Shoot Down!

2
00:00:12,583 --> 00:00:15,666
[CROWD cheering]

3
00:00:17,833 --> 00:00:20,625
[MAN 1] Kita High was
knocked out in the first round?

4
00:00:20,708 --> 00:00:22,916
Zero wins.
Three losses in a row.

5
00:00:23,000 --> 00:00:24,208
That's gotta hurt.

6
00:00:26,708 --> 00:00:28,250
[TENMA crying]

7
00:00:28,333 --> 00:00:29,958
I failed everyone.

8
00:00:30,041 --> 00:00:31,666
[YONEMURA]
Snap out of it, Tenma.

9
00:00:31,750 --> 00:00:33,708
You've still got
the individual tournament,

10
00:00:33,791 --> 00:00:35,541
and you can compete
next year, too.

11
00:00:36,666 --> 00:00:38,375
What about you guys, though?

12
00:00:38,458 --> 00:00:40,000
This was your last chance!

13
00:00:43,083 --> 00:00:45,541
Not one of you is pathetic!

14
00:00:45,625 --> 00:00:48,416
Not my team, the school,
or my brother.

15
00:00:48,500 --> 00:00:50,208
All three of those
give me pride!

16
00:00:51,583 --> 00:00:53,000
I wanted to show the world that!

17
00:00:54,000 --> 00:00:55,041
And I failed!

18
00:00:55,125 --> 00:00:57,291
[laughs]
Don't hold back, Tenma.

19
00:00:57,375 --> 00:00:59,583
Why don't tell us
how you really feel?

20
00:00:59,666 --> 00:01:02,833
Look. Everyone, including you,
did the best they could.

21
00:01:04,916 --> 00:01:06,708
In the end, it wasn't enough.

22
00:01:06,791 --> 00:01:09,833
And that's a hard pill
to swallow.

23
00:01:11,083 --> 00:01:14,208
People will tell us we'll look
back on this day and smile.

24
00:01:14,291 --> 00:01:15,541
But they weren't here.

25
00:01:15,625 --> 00:01:17,708
They didn't fight!
We did!

26
00:01:19,958 --> 00:01:22,291
[SHUNKAI] A sweeping loss
can be difficult to take.

27
00:01:23,291 --> 00:01:26,208
But your pain reveals
how sincere the effort was.

28
00:01:27,958 --> 00:01:30,125
Victory is always preferable.

29
00:01:30,208 --> 00:01:32,333
But there's value
in accepting defeat.

30
00:01:32,416 --> 00:01:35,916
Use this moment
and grow as warriors.

31
00:01:39,166 --> 00:01:40,375
[ANNOUNCER]
Match over.

32
00:01:40,458 --> 00:01:43,041
Odachi, on the east side,
wins three-zero.

33
00:01:43,125 --> 00:01:45,666
[CROWD cheering, applauding]

34
00:01:45,750 --> 00:01:47,041
[TENNOJI]
You can't help but admit,

35
00:01:47,125 --> 00:01:49,125
they make an impressive team.

36
00:01:49,208 --> 00:01:51,458
They're uneven,
but they've got momentum.

37
00:01:51,541 --> 00:01:53,083
Don't underestimate them.

38
00:01:53,166 --> 00:01:54,875
I won't deny they're special.

39
00:01:54,958 --> 00:01:57,041
But how many have we seen
just like 'em?

40
00:01:57,125 --> 00:01:58,541
This happens every year.

41
00:01:58,625 --> 00:02:02,041
A team gathers a little steam,
wins a few matches,

42
00:02:02,125 --> 00:02:04,583
then acts like they've got
what it takes to go all the way.

43
00:02:05,750 --> 00:02:07,166
Some wrestlers.

44
00:02:07,250 --> 00:02:09,250
Well, they even become
national treasures.

45
00:02:09,333 --> 00:02:10,875
We're used to devouring
their kind

46
00:02:10,958 --> 00:02:13,000
and nothing's changing that.

47
00:02:13,083 --> 00:02:14,416
Right?

48
00:02:14,500 --> 00:02:15,916
Damn straight.

49
00:03:47,041 --> 00:03:49,166
[ANNOUNCER]
Team tournament, round three.

50
00:03:49,250 --> 00:03:51,791
On the east side,
Kabutoyama High School.

51
00:03:51,875 --> 00:03:54,125
On the west side,
Odachi High School.

52
00:03:54,208 --> 00:03:56,625
[yelling]

53
00:03:56,708 --> 00:03:59,291
[straining]

54
00:03:59,375 --> 00:04:00,583
Yes!

55
00:04:00,666 --> 00:04:02,750
[YUMA grunting]

56
00:04:04,708 --> 00:04:05,708
Yeah!

57
00:04:06,708 --> 00:04:08,875
[HINOMARU grunting]

58
00:04:08,958 --> 00:04:11,125
[MAN 2] Three for three
in the third round!

59
00:04:11,208 --> 00:04:13,041
With yesterday's momentum
and Hinomaru back,

60
00:04:13,125 --> 00:04:14,750
they're unstoppable!

61
00:04:14,833 --> 00:04:17,041
[MAN 3] That left arm doesn't
seem to be bothering him either.

62
00:04:17,125 --> 00:04:19,416
Odachi could be the champs
this year!

63
00:04:19,500 --> 00:04:21,166
[ANNOUNCER] Fourth bout.
On the east side, Yamada.

64
00:04:21,250 --> 00:04:22,291
Hold on.

65
00:04:22,375 --> 00:04:23,833
Didn't we just win
three in a row?

66
00:04:23,916 --> 00:04:25,416
Why are there more matches?

67
00:04:25,500 --> 00:04:27,041
Starting today, we have to fight

68
00:04:27,125 --> 00:04:29,208
all five bouts in each round.

69
00:04:29,291 --> 00:04:30,375
[MAN 2]
He got behind him!

70
00:04:31,458 --> 00:04:32,791
That's four!

71
00:04:34,250 --> 00:04:35,166
All right.

72
00:04:35,250 --> 00:04:37,625
This is it, your national debut!

73
00:04:38,708 --> 00:04:40,041
[ANNOUNCER]
Fifth bout.

74
00:04:40,125 --> 00:04:41,666
On the east side, Sato.

75
00:04:41,750 --> 00:04:43,583
On the west side, Mitsuhashi.

76
00:04:43,666 --> 00:04:45,125
[MAN 2]
Where's the rest of him?

77
00:04:45,208 --> 00:04:46,916
[MAN 3]
I saw this guy at the prelims.

78
00:04:47,000 --> 00:04:49,041
He makes a charge
then does a surprise leap.

79
00:04:50,041 --> 00:04:51,875
The shrimp's devious!
Be careful!

80
00:04:51,958 --> 00:04:53,041
Mmm.

81
00:04:57,166 --> 00:04:58,416
[REFEREE]
Spirit!

82
00:04:58,500 --> 00:05:00,208
-[SATO] No tricks this time.
-[KEI screams]

83
00:05:00,291 --> 00:05:02,208
[SATO] Did you think
we wouldn't catch on?

84
00:05:04,291 --> 00:05:05,333
[MAN 2]
Big surprise.

85
00:05:05,416 --> 00:05:07,125
But he never gives up.

86
00:05:08,708 --> 00:05:10,250
Good effort.

87
00:05:10,333 --> 00:05:11,916
[KEI]
I'll be fine.

88
00:05:12,000 --> 00:05:13,541
It's a matter of time.

89
00:05:13,625 --> 00:05:15,000
I'll win with a change-up.

90
00:05:16,083 --> 00:05:17,125
Mmm.

91
00:05:23,916 --> 00:05:26,583
Why are you yawning?
You better've slept.

92
00:05:26,666 --> 00:05:28,708
I may have stayed up late
watching some footage

93
00:05:28,791 --> 00:05:30,500
from the Nagoya Tournament.

94
00:05:30,583 --> 00:05:32,708
Daikeisho was so close
to winning it.

95
00:05:32,791 --> 00:05:34,875
Hah! Keep dreaming.

96
00:05:34,958 --> 00:05:36,625
Japanese fighters are weak.

97
00:05:36,708 --> 00:05:38,583
They don't stand a chance
against Mongolian

98
00:05:38,666 --> 00:05:39,833
or Jino wrestlers.

99
00:05:39,916 --> 00:05:42,000
[ENOKI] We get it.
You made your point.

100
00:05:42,083 --> 00:05:43,625
But that's why
we're here, right?

101
00:05:43,708 --> 00:05:45,208
To get stronger.

102
00:05:45,291 --> 00:05:46,208
Hmm?

103
00:05:48,125 --> 00:05:49,541
It's Kusanagi.

104
00:05:49,625 --> 00:05:51,750
Well, well, Dojikiri.

105
00:05:51,833 --> 00:05:53,791
I prefer Tennoji.

106
00:05:53,875 --> 00:05:56,500
I've never been fond of
my national treasure moniker.

107
00:05:56,583 --> 00:05:58,375
Yours on the other hand.

108
00:05:58,458 --> 00:06:01,666
"Kusanagi," that's a way
cooler-sounding name.

109
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:03,833
I guess being the son
of a yokozuna,

110
00:06:03,916 --> 00:06:05,166
people expect more out of you

111
00:06:05,250 --> 00:06:07,000
than the rest of us
mere mortals.

112
00:06:08,041 --> 00:06:10,250
But hey, when you step
in the ring,

113
00:06:10,333 --> 00:06:12,416
your father and moniker
can't follow.

114
00:06:12,500 --> 00:06:15,291
Once inside,
you're there all alone.

115
00:06:16,875 --> 00:06:19,541
Tennoji, you're wrong.

116
00:06:19,625 --> 00:06:22,541
As a yokozuna's son,
I always carry that weight.

117
00:06:22,625 --> 00:06:24,041
Wherever I go.

118
00:06:24,125 --> 00:06:26,666
[chuckling]
One thing's certain,

119
00:06:26,750 --> 00:06:29,208
this year's inter-high
has no shortage of thrills.

120
00:06:30,208 --> 00:06:32,833
[ANNOUNCEMENT] On the east side,
Tottori Hakuro High School.

121
00:06:32,916 --> 00:06:34,416
[MAN 3]
It was a matter of time.

122
00:06:34,500 --> 00:06:36,166
Here come the showstoppers.

123
00:06:37,166 --> 00:06:38,333
[ANNOUNCER]
First bout.

124
00:06:38,416 --> 00:06:40,708
On the east side, Enoki.

125
00:06:40,791 --> 00:06:41,875
[REFEREE]
Spirit!

126
00:06:45,000 --> 00:06:46,291
[grunts]

127
00:06:47,958 --> 00:06:49,833
What the heck kinda move
was that?

128
00:06:49,916 --> 00:06:52,458
It's a skill used in aikido.

129
00:06:52,541 --> 00:06:55,375
Sumo's all about knocking
your opponent off-balance.

130
00:06:55,458 --> 00:06:57,208
Hakuro's wrestler
isn't that tall

131
00:06:57,291 --> 00:06:58,958
and doesn't have
a large frame.

132
00:06:59,041 --> 00:07:02,250
So he targets an opponent's
center of gravity to compensate.

133
00:07:03,750 --> 00:07:05,666
There's a reason
their team's the best.

134
00:07:05,750 --> 00:07:08,166
It's because they employ
a wide range of techniques.

135
00:07:09,166 --> 00:07:12,000
I chose this school because
of its colorful characters.

136
00:07:12,083 --> 00:07:14,125
Hakuro's team has
my kind of people.

137
00:07:15,125 --> 00:07:16,750
[REINA]
What're you saying?

138
00:07:16,833 --> 00:07:19,458
Some specialize
in the technical, like Enoki.

139
00:07:20,541 --> 00:07:21,750
[ANNOUNCER]
Second bout.

140
00:07:21,833 --> 00:07:24,000
On the east side, Shuto.

141
00:07:25,875 --> 00:07:28,000
[CHIZUKO] While others are
all about brute strength.

142
00:07:28,083 --> 00:07:31,125
Each one's different,
but they're all experts.

143
00:07:31,208 --> 00:07:34,125
Every year, we have several
interesting sumo wrestlers

144
00:07:34,208 --> 00:07:36,666
who decide to enroll
at our school.

145
00:07:36,750 --> 00:07:39,541
Even International students
from Mongolia.

146
00:07:39,625 --> 00:07:41,416
It lends the team some variety.

147
00:07:42,500 --> 00:07:45,000
We motivate each other to win.

148
00:07:45,083 --> 00:07:46,916
From the bottom of my heart,

149
00:07:47,000 --> 00:07:48,833
I'm glad to be a part of Hakuro.

150
00:07:50,625 --> 00:07:52,333
[YUMA] They opened up
the practice area.

151
00:07:52,416 --> 00:07:53,458
We should check it out.

152
00:07:53,541 --> 00:07:54,625
[CHIHIRO]
It's not going anywhere.

153
00:07:54,708 --> 00:07:56,041
Let's find grub first.

154
00:07:56,125 --> 00:07:57,916
[SADA] Sounds like
you're in good spirits.

155
00:07:58,000 --> 00:07:59,583
Not even Hakuro scares you, huh?

156
00:08:00,875 --> 00:08:02,833
-[HINOMARU] Sada?
-If you're headed to practice,

157
00:08:03,833 --> 00:08:05,500
you don't mind
if we join, right?

158
00:08:05,583 --> 00:08:07,041
[SADA laughs]

159
00:08:07,125 --> 00:08:09,375
Come on.
Don't look so suspicious.

160
00:08:09,458 --> 00:08:11,875
After the prelims,
we actually took a trip.

161
00:08:11,958 --> 00:08:14,041
Just a stop in Tottori,
nothing big.

162
00:08:14,125 --> 00:08:15,416
Wait. Tottori?

163
00:08:15,500 --> 00:08:16,625
Then you mean...

164
00:08:16,708 --> 00:08:18,083
But if you guys
would rather eat,

165
00:08:18,166 --> 00:08:20,166
then how about for dessert

166
00:08:20,250 --> 00:08:23,000
we tell you what it was like
taking on the great Hakuro High?

167
00:08:24,166 --> 00:08:26,333
[ANNOUNCER]
The 32 qualifying competitors

168
00:08:26,416 --> 00:08:29,583
will begin the final rounds
of the individual tournament.

169
00:08:29,666 --> 00:08:32,041
[CROWD cheering]

170
00:08:33,458 --> 00:08:36,000
[SADA] Okay.
Let's get this thing started.

171
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:39,916
I formally declare this
"The Ishi Slash Dachi High

172
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,958
Sparring Session
to Take Down Hakuro!"

173
00:08:42,041 --> 00:08:43,833
We're actually working with 'em?

174
00:08:43,916 --> 00:08:46,208
This is like
full-on treason, man!

175
00:08:46,291 --> 00:08:48,000
Why should we do them
any favors?

176
00:08:48,083 --> 00:08:50,083
-[KANAMORI groans]
-[SANADA] Hmm?

177
00:08:50,166 --> 00:08:52,708
He's right.
We are a rival team after all.

178
00:08:52,791 --> 00:08:54,333
Why would you want to help us?

179
00:08:54,416 --> 00:08:56,208
Because, when all's said
and done,

180
00:08:56,291 --> 00:08:58,666
Ishi High's going
to benefit huge.

181
00:08:58,750 --> 00:09:00,875
-Yeah? How?
-[SADA] New Captain Mamiya.

182
00:09:00,958 --> 00:09:03,625
Please explain it to them
in excruciating detail.

183
00:09:03,708 --> 00:09:05,541
Sure, leave all
the exposition to me.

184
00:09:05,625 --> 00:09:07,500
I don't mind one bit.

185
00:09:07,583 --> 00:09:09,333
While it's true
this could strengthen Dachi High

186
00:09:09,416 --> 00:09:11,166
and bite us in the ass,

187
00:09:11,250 --> 00:09:13,166
if you keep pushing them,

188
00:09:13,250 --> 00:09:14,500
Hakuro will have no choice

189
00:09:14,583 --> 00:09:16,958
but to dig deeper
and reveal their range,

190
00:09:17,041 --> 00:09:19,541
which will prepare us
for when we eventually face off.

191
00:09:20,625 --> 00:09:22,458
You think it'll actually work?

192
00:09:22,541 --> 00:09:24,875
[MAMIYA] You benefited
from testing Kunisaki's limits.

193
00:09:24,958 --> 00:09:26,208
Isn't that right, Sada?

194
00:09:26,291 --> 00:09:28,708
Yeah.
I can't deny it.

195
00:09:28,791 --> 00:09:30,791
I stole as much
as I could from him.

196
00:09:30,875 --> 00:09:32,958
He's not the only one
with an appetite for moves.

197
00:09:34,416 --> 00:09:37,208
[YUMA] Don't expect us
to thank you or anything.

198
00:09:37,291 --> 00:09:40,000
Since we both get something
out of it, I say we accept.

199
00:09:40,083 --> 00:09:42,333
Still, I hate the idea
of giving Dachi High

200
00:09:42,416 --> 00:09:44,833
more opportunities to celebrate!

201
00:09:44,916 --> 00:09:46,208
Isn't that the truth?

202
00:09:46,291 --> 00:09:47,958
No offense, but it wasn't
that long ago

203
00:09:48,041 --> 00:09:49,708
your team was pathetic.

204
00:09:49,791 --> 00:09:52,833
Ozeki was the only member
and always lost the first round.

205
00:09:52,916 --> 00:09:54,291
[chuckles nervously]

206
00:09:54,375 --> 00:09:56,875
And now you're standing
in the national spotlight.

207
00:09:56,958 --> 00:09:58,458
There's a word for that.

208
00:09:58,541 --> 00:09:59,583
-Incredible.
-Huh?

209
00:10:00,666 --> 00:10:02,833
[SANADA] Any animosity
we feel for you as rivals

210
00:10:02,916 --> 00:10:05,333
is only matched
by our respect.

211
00:10:05,416 --> 00:10:08,208
We aren't doing this solely
for our own benefit.

212
00:10:09,625 --> 00:10:12,250
We want you to go far.
Sound good?

213
00:10:12,333 --> 00:10:14,625
♪

214
00:10:15,875 --> 00:10:18,291
I'm the stand-in for Tennoji?

215
00:10:18,375 --> 00:10:19,666
That's flattering.

216
00:10:19,750 --> 00:10:22,291
It's just so Ushio
can visualize him.

217
00:10:22,375 --> 00:10:25,166
And out of everyone,
your physique's the closest.

218
00:10:25,250 --> 00:10:26,875
[KANAMORI]
I get ya.

219
00:10:26,958 --> 00:10:29,125
[SANADA] If you don't want to do
this, you don't have to, Araki.

220
00:10:29,208 --> 00:10:31,416
[SADA] Yeah, don't feel
pressured if you're not down.

221
00:10:31,500 --> 00:10:33,125
You'd like that, wouldn't you?

222
00:10:33,208 --> 00:10:35,458
-Leaving me out!
[laughing]

223
00:10:36,458 --> 00:10:37,833
[KIRIHITO]
Having a double for Tennoji

224
00:10:37,916 --> 00:10:39,541
will go a long way for Ushio.

225
00:10:41,000 --> 00:10:43,000
I'm sure their session
will help him grow.

226
00:10:44,000 --> 00:10:45,125
And yet...

227
00:10:46,208 --> 00:10:48,458
We can't start thinking
Hakuro is the only thing

228
00:10:48,541 --> 00:10:50,375
standing between us
and the crown.

229
00:10:53,166 --> 00:10:54,166
There's another.

230
00:10:55,208 --> 00:10:57,041
From Eiga University High.

231
00:10:58,083 --> 00:10:59,750
Sosuke Kuze.

232
00:10:59,833 --> 00:11:02,958
The son of a Yokozuna,
and right at the age

233
00:11:03,041 --> 00:11:05,625
when you naturally want
to defy your parents.

234
00:11:05,708 --> 00:11:07,708
If you want my opinion,

235
00:11:07,791 --> 00:11:10,375
he's got the same bearing
you did at your peak.

236
00:11:10,458 --> 00:11:12,166
But maybe I'm just imagining it.

237
00:11:12,250 --> 00:11:14,666
From what I hear, he plans
to join the pro league

238
00:11:14,750 --> 00:11:17,041
after he becomes
the high school yokozuna.

239
00:11:17,125 --> 00:11:20,250
The fact it doesn't come across
as a joke is scary.

240
00:11:20,333 --> 00:11:23,291
I'm the biggest supporter
of my son.

241
00:11:23,375 --> 00:11:25,875
For the longest time, the
thought of anyone his own age

242
00:11:25,958 --> 00:11:27,791
posing a challenge
was unthinkable.

243
00:11:28,791 --> 00:11:30,458
That is, until now.

244
00:11:31,625 --> 00:11:34,041
[ANNOUNCER] The individual
tournament semifinal.

245
00:11:34,125 --> 00:11:35,916
On the east side, Tennoji.

246
00:11:36,000 --> 00:11:38,541
On the west side, Kuze.

247
00:11:38,625 --> 00:11:40,916
But whatever the outcome
is today...

248
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:44,291
[CROWD cheering]

249
00:11:44,375 --> 00:11:47,875
...the future of pro sumo
is brilliant.

250
00:11:47,958 --> 00:11:50,750
Hey. How come everybody's
losing their minds?

251
00:11:50,833 --> 00:11:54,041
Because it's like watching
two yokozuna fight.

252
00:11:55,166 --> 00:11:57,458
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
The son of Yamatokuni.

253
00:11:57,541 --> 00:11:59,125
Undefeated in official bouts

254
00:11:59,208 --> 00:12:00,916
and on the path
to being a champion.

255
00:12:02,125 --> 00:12:05,208
Facing off against
the battle-hardened conqueror.

256
00:12:05,291 --> 00:12:07,166
This will decide who's best.

257
00:12:10,583 --> 00:12:11,416
[REFEREE]
Spirit!

258
00:12:11,500 --> 00:12:12,833
[BOTH grunt]

259
00:12:15,458 --> 00:12:17,875
[CROWD cheering]

260
00:12:17,958 --> 00:12:20,791
♪

261
00:12:20,875 --> 00:12:22,583
[KIRIHITO]
Truth be told, I'd rather

262
00:12:22,666 --> 00:12:24,083
these two didn't fight
each other.

263
00:12:25,375 --> 00:12:28,875
They're already fearsome,
but together, in a bout.

264
00:12:28,958 --> 00:12:30,750
No telling what it'll unleash.

265
00:12:30,833 --> 00:12:31,875
♪

266
00:12:31,958 --> 00:12:33,875
[clock ticking]

267
00:12:33,958 --> 00:12:35,166
[SHUNKAI]
Your mind's wandering.

268
00:12:36,208 --> 00:12:37,875
Which one will be triumphant?

269
00:12:39,583 --> 00:12:42,208
It doesn't matter, because
they've left you in their wake.

270
00:12:42,291 --> 00:12:44,208
Not to mention
when the dust clears,

271
00:12:44,291 --> 00:12:46,708
this fight might put you
even further behind

272
00:12:47,958 --> 00:12:50,541
So, how do you plan
on winning tomorrow

273
00:12:50,625 --> 00:12:53,500
if you already gave it your all
and it still wasn't enough?

274
00:12:54,708 --> 00:12:56,958
Exactly how you taught me.

275
00:12:57,041 --> 00:12:58,000
I've been thinking.

276
00:12:59,166 --> 00:13:01,333
Back to the moment I lost.

277
00:13:01,416 --> 00:13:03,333
Even going all out against him,

278
00:13:03,416 --> 00:13:05,666
I never saw the limit
of Tennoji's power.

279
00:13:07,875 --> 00:13:10,333
But thanks to everybody
in this room,

280
00:13:10,416 --> 00:13:12,083
I've had this revelation.

281
00:13:12,166 --> 00:13:14,541
There's something hidden
inside me.

282
00:13:14,625 --> 00:13:18,208
A source of strength I haven't
managed to tap into... yet.

283
00:13:19,208 --> 00:13:21,708
Sada, we need to have a bout.

284
00:13:21,791 --> 00:13:23,750
-No holding back.
-[chuckles]

285
00:13:24,750 --> 00:13:26,958
In order to get closer to them,

286
00:13:27,041 --> 00:13:29,625
what I need to do
is take another step forward!

287
00:13:30,875 --> 00:13:33,083
Very well, then.
Let's see what you've got.

288
00:13:33,166 --> 00:13:37,500
♪

289
00:13:37,583 --> 00:13:39,291
[SHUNKAI] Out of everyone,
you're best suited

290
00:13:39,375 --> 00:13:41,583
for discovering
your own style of fighting.

291
00:13:42,875 --> 00:13:47,750
Now, show me the new
and improved Hinomaru sumo!

292
00:13:47,833 --> 00:13:51,125
♪

293
00:13:51,208 --> 00:13:53,708
[grunting]

294
00:13:53,791 --> 00:13:55,208
That's a leg technique!

295
00:13:55,291 --> 00:13:58,083
♪

296
00:13:58,166 --> 00:13:59,375
[KIRIHITO]
Based on what I've seen,

297
00:13:59,458 --> 00:14:01,333
I thought Tennoji
would be more composed.

298
00:14:02,333 --> 00:14:04,208
But it's like
he's a different person!

299
00:14:05,583 --> 00:14:07,500
[SADA]
Tennoji has two faces.

300
00:14:09,250 --> 00:14:11,041
When we sparred in Tottori,

301
00:14:11,125 --> 00:14:13,375
I got the chance to see both.

302
00:14:13,458 --> 00:14:16,416
The first, he uses
to avoid losing.

303
00:14:16,500 --> 00:14:18,125
He watches his opponent,

304
00:14:18,208 --> 00:14:19,875
then carefully selects
a strategy

305
00:14:19,958 --> 00:14:21,291
that'll give him an advantage.

306
00:14:22,291 --> 00:14:24,875
The guy researches endlessly
and builds an approach

307
00:14:24,958 --> 00:14:26,875
that plays the percentage game.

308
00:14:26,958 --> 00:14:29,583
That's how he stayed undefeated
throughout high school.

309
00:14:29,666 --> 00:14:32,041
But something happened
two years ago.

310
00:14:32,125 --> 00:14:35,000
He had to fight upperclassmen
who were stronger than he was.

311
00:14:35,083 --> 00:14:38,333
His second face
is all about winning.

312
00:14:38,416 --> 00:14:41,083
I prefer using
a more defensive style,

313
00:14:41,166 --> 00:14:43,708
counterattacking moves
my opponents make.

314
00:14:43,791 --> 00:14:45,250
I'm good.

315
00:14:45,333 --> 00:14:47,625
But when I forced Tennoji
to go on the offensive...

316
00:14:49,041 --> 00:14:52,500
the barrage of attacks he rained
down on me was nonstop.

317
00:14:52,583 --> 00:14:54,791
Completely without mercy.

318
00:14:54,875 --> 00:14:57,583
Thinking about it now
sends chills down my spine.

319
00:14:59,083 --> 00:15:00,500
[TENNOJI grunts]

320
00:15:02,625 --> 00:15:04,500
[KARIYA]
So this is Dojikiri.

321
00:15:05,541 --> 00:15:06,916
The champion.

322
00:15:07,000 --> 00:15:09,041
In his bout with Onimaru...

323
00:15:09,125 --> 00:15:11,958
No, he didn't waver
in any match, even that one.

324
00:15:12,041 --> 00:15:13,750
I'm worried about Sosuke.

325
00:15:14,791 --> 00:15:16,000
He may lose.

326
00:15:17,583 --> 00:15:19,291
To the best of my knowledge,

327
00:15:19,375 --> 00:15:21,791
Shido Tennoji is
the strongest sumo wrestler

328
00:15:21,875 --> 00:15:24,666
currently competing
at the high school level.

329
00:15:24,750 --> 00:15:27,208
However, no one in that arena,

330
00:15:28,250 --> 00:15:29,791
even including me,

331
00:15:29,875 --> 00:15:32,875
knows the true limits
of Sosuke Kuze's strength.

332
00:15:35,916 --> 00:15:37,125
[TENNOJI]
Yamatokuni?

333
00:15:38,166 --> 00:15:39,875
[KUZE]
What's going on?

334
00:15:39,958 --> 00:15:42,208
My blood should be boiling.

335
00:15:42,291 --> 00:15:44,041
And yet, nothing.

336
00:15:44,125 --> 00:15:45,583
I'm completely calm.

337
00:15:45,666 --> 00:15:48,208
[SHIBAKIYAMA] He's always
compared to his father,

338
00:15:48,291 --> 00:15:49,958
but it's finally starting
to come true.

339
00:15:50,958 --> 00:15:53,791
He's not like Hinomaru
or Tennoji.

340
00:15:53,875 --> 00:15:57,208
The most terrifying thing
about him is his stillness

341
00:15:57,291 --> 00:15:59,791
and eyes that reveal
an unwavering strength.

342
00:16:00,791 --> 00:16:02,791
He's completely serene.

343
00:16:03,833 --> 00:16:06,625
[SAKI] Whenever you attack,
it creates openings.

344
00:16:06,708 --> 00:16:08,791
My brother calls that
a weakness.

345
00:16:08,875 --> 00:16:10,875
But when he used to throw
defense out the window

346
00:16:10,958 --> 00:16:13,041
and fought only on instinct,

347
00:16:13,125 --> 00:16:15,000
he was much scarier.

348
00:16:15,083 --> 00:16:16,208
Like a demon!

349
00:16:17,416 --> 00:16:19,208
[HINOMARU]
It doesn't matter who wins.

350
00:16:19,291 --> 00:16:20,916
My path's already been laid out.

351
00:16:22,041 --> 00:16:24,125
[SADA]
Hinomaru Ushio.

352
00:16:24,208 --> 00:16:26,833
Don't ever stop surprising me!

353
00:16:26,916 --> 00:16:27,916
Let's go!

354
00:16:28,000 --> 00:16:29,250
[HINOMARU]
Sada!

355
00:16:29,333 --> 00:16:30,250
Thank you!

356
00:16:34,166 --> 00:16:35,583
[KIRIHITO]
They've moved back.

357
00:16:35,666 --> 00:16:37,291
This could be it.

358
00:16:37,375 --> 00:16:38,375
Here's the charge.

359
00:16:38,458 --> 00:16:40,250
This might be the one to end it!

360
00:16:41,291 --> 00:16:42,250
[TENNOJI groans]

361
00:16:42,333 --> 00:16:43,708
That's Kusanagi's!

362
00:16:43,791 --> 00:16:45,791
They were evenly matched
on the first charge!

363
00:16:45,875 --> 00:16:47,750
Tennoji's strength
must've awakened

364
00:16:47,833 --> 00:16:49,541
the beast in Sosuke!

365
00:16:49,625 --> 00:16:50,541
It's on now!

366
00:16:53,166 --> 00:16:54,458
He dodged it?

367
00:16:54,541 --> 00:16:56,291
[TENNOJI] If you think
you have the upper hand,

368
00:16:56,375 --> 00:16:57,375
you're wrong.

369
00:16:59,375 --> 00:17:01,750
The beast inside of me
has risen!

370
00:17:01,833 --> 00:17:02,916
♪

371
00:17:03,000 --> 00:17:04,208
[SAKI]
There it is.

372
00:17:04,291 --> 00:17:06,125
The super-low attack
my brother perfected

373
00:17:06,208 --> 00:17:07,375
when he was Ushio's height.

374
00:17:08,416 --> 00:17:11,125
Only he can pull it off
because he used to be short.

375
00:17:12,125 --> 00:17:14,666
-Its intensity is boundless!
-[KUZE groans]

376
00:17:16,500 --> 00:17:17,500
[KARIYA]
Not good!

377
00:17:17,583 --> 00:17:19,291
He's taking too many hits!

378
00:17:19,375 --> 00:17:21,458
Every one of them
from a champion.

379
00:17:22,541 --> 00:17:24,708
It's breaking him,
piece by piece!

380
00:17:25,708 --> 00:17:27,291
[TENNOJI]
All those years of being small

381
00:17:27,375 --> 00:17:29,333
made me the wrestler I am today.

382
00:17:30,750 --> 00:17:33,125
This moment will have
the same effect.

383
00:17:33,208 --> 00:17:34,958
Making me the strongest!

384
00:17:36,583 --> 00:17:38,958
I'm battling a copy
of Yamatokuni,

385
00:17:39,041 --> 00:17:41,333
the greatest yokozuna
of the Heisei era.

386
00:17:42,416 --> 00:17:43,750
This is a trial.

387
00:17:43,833 --> 00:17:46,125
Another task the sumo gods
have arranged for me

388
00:17:46,208 --> 00:17:47,833
to become the best
in the world!

389
00:17:47,916 --> 00:17:48,958
He locked his arm!

390
00:17:49,041 --> 00:17:50,875
It's Tennoji's game!

391
00:17:50,958 --> 00:17:53,416
[TENNOJI] You're just
an obstacle to overcome!

392
00:17:53,500 --> 00:17:55,666
Soon, I'll wear the rope
that tells everyone

393
00:17:55,750 --> 00:17:58,083
I defeated
the legendary Yamatokuni!

394
00:18:00,958 --> 00:18:02,958
What a fearsome competitor!

395
00:18:03,041 --> 00:18:04,791
Even in the face
of incredible pressure,

396
00:18:04,875 --> 00:18:06,416
he's still thinking.

397
00:18:06,500 --> 00:18:08,583
Calculating how he can win
against his opponent

398
00:18:08,666 --> 00:18:10,916
using his style of sumo.

399
00:18:11,000 --> 00:18:12,166
It's...

400
00:18:12,250 --> 00:18:14,291
[KUZE]
My right hand's on his belt.

401
00:18:14,375 --> 00:18:17,708
This is the strongest form
I inherited from my father.

402
00:18:17,791 --> 00:18:21,875
For me, the sumo gods are part
of Yamatokuni's fighting style!

403
00:18:22,916 --> 00:18:24,666
[TENNOJI]
That was expected.

404
00:18:24,750 --> 00:18:26,750
I've given up on defense
after all.

405
00:18:26,833 --> 00:18:29,625
It was necessary
if I was going to reach the top!

406
00:18:29,708 --> 00:18:31,000
An arm lock throw!

407
00:18:31,083 --> 00:18:32,291
And an overarm throw!

408
00:18:32,375 --> 00:18:33,916
[SAKI/KARIYA]
At the same time!

409
00:18:34,000 --> 00:18:35,833
[BOTH yelling]

410
00:18:35,916 --> 00:18:37,916
[TENNOJI]
Six Point Torso Slice!

411
00:18:38,000 --> 00:18:39,666
[KUZE]
Great Serpent Cleaver!

412
00:18:39,750 --> 00:18:41,041
-[thudding]
-[BOTH gasp]

413
00:18:41,125 --> 00:18:42,541
[ALL gasp]

414
00:18:42,625 --> 00:18:43,916
[BOTH gasp]

415
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:45,041
[SANADA gasps]

416
00:18:46,500 --> 00:18:48,250
[SHUNKAI] I wondered
if the sumo gods turned

417
00:18:48,333 --> 00:18:49,916
their gaze away from him.

418
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:51,750
He wasn't blessed with height.

419
00:18:52,791 --> 00:18:54,041
Yet his spirit, body,

420
00:18:54,125 --> 00:18:56,875
and technique
all have room to grow.

421
00:18:56,958 --> 00:18:58,583
Then, I saw it.

422
00:18:58,666 --> 00:19:00,125
It surrounded him.

423
00:19:01,625 --> 00:19:02,833
A light.

424
00:19:02,916 --> 00:19:05,708
So that's why the sumo gods
looked away.

425
00:19:05,791 --> 00:19:07,500
They'd been blinded!

426
00:19:08,750 --> 00:19:10,041
Incredible.

427
00:19:10,125 --> 00:19:11,916
It could be the edge he needed.

428
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:13,041
Just might.

429
00:19:15,250 --> 00:19:17,041
[KIRIHITO]
Looks like it paid off.

430
00:19:17,125 --> 00:19:18,208
Is the match over?

431
00:19:18,291 --> 00:19:19,625
Who won, Coach?

432
00:19:19,708 --> 00:19:21,250
Tennoji or Kuze?

433
00:19:22,541 --> 00:19:23,666
Come take a look.

434
00:19:23,750 --> 00:19:26,041
♪

435
00:19:26,125 --> 00:19:31,375
[BOTH grunting]

436
00:19:36,166 --> 00:19:37,958
[SHIBAKIYAMA]
A yokozuna.

437
00:19:38,041 --> 00:19:40,791
The only person permitted
to wear a sacred rope

438
00:19:40,875 --> 00:19:42,166
on their body.

439
00:19:42,250 --> 00:19:44,208
They are divine objects.

440
00:19:45,208 --> 00:19:48,125
It's evident Shido Tennoji
was loved by the gods.

441
00:19:48,208 --> 00:19:49,833
♪

442
00:19:49,916 --> 00:19:51,625
Sosuke Kuze...

443
00:19:51,708 --> 00:19:53,041
Kusanagi...

444
00:19:53,125 --> 00:19:54,166
was not.

445
00:19:56,375 --> 00:19:58,375
He is a god.

446
00:19:58,458 --> 00:20:01,000
An embodiment of the divine.

447
00:20:01,083 --> 00:20:03,375
And will reign
over the sumo ring.

448
00:20:05,583 --> 00:20:06,916
He won.

449
00:20:07,000 --> 00:20:08,375
Still, it's not like
we're just gonna wimp out

450
00:20:08,458 --> 00:20:09,500
‘cause that happened.

451
00:20:09,583 --> 00:20:11,375
We planned
to beat Tennoji, Kuze,

452
00:20:11,458 --> 00:20:13,000
and all the rest anyway!

453
00:20:13,083 --> 00:20:14,458
And that hasn't changed!

454
00:20:14,541 --> 00:20:15,583
[ALL]
Hmm.

455
00:20:18,625 --> 00:20:21,000
[HINOMARU]
Ahh! I lost again?

456
00:20:21,083 --> 00:20:22,583
Rematch! One more game!

457
00:20:22,666 --> 00:20:25,000
[CHIHIRO chuckles]
Don't ever go gambling.

458
00:20:25,083 --> 00:20:26,416
[HINOMARU]
Come on, Yuma!

459
00:20:26,500 --> 00:20:27,625
Cut the cards better!

460
00:20:27,708 --> 00:20:29,583
You aren't doing
anything shady, are you?

461
00:20:29,666 --> 00:20:30,958
[YUMA]
No. You just suck.

462
00:20:31,041 --> 00:20:32,500
[OZEKI laughs]

463
00:20:32,583 --> 00:20:34,708
This game won't be over
until Ushio wins at least once.

464
00:20:34,791 --> 00:20:37,375
I think you're supposed to keep
your eyes on your own cards?

465
00:20:37,458 --> 00:20:38,875
[CHIHIRO]
Loosen up, amigo!

466
00:20:38,958 --> 00:20:40,416
Seeing how relaxed they are,

467
00:20:40,500 --> 00:20:42,875
you'd have no idea the finals
were happening tomorrow.

468
00:20:42,958 --> 00:20:43,791
Hmm?

469
00:20:43,875 --> 00:20:45,208
Shouldn't they be,

470
00:20:45,291 --> 00:20:47,083
like, sweating bullets?

471
00:20:47,166 --> 00:20:48,458
[KIRIHITO]
Just the opposite.

472
00:20:48,541 --> 00:20:49,750
If the guys were nervous,

473
00:20:49,833 --> 00:20:51,458
none of them would last
through the night.

474
00:20:51,541 --> 00:20:53,125
This is a good sign.

475
00:20:53,208 --> 00:20:55,958
There's no need to worry about
their mental state anymore.

476
00:20:57,041 --> 00:20:58,708
I remember the old days.

477
00:20:58,791 --> 00:21:01,583
You got so worked up,
saying you wouldn't lose,

478
00:21:01,666 --> 00:21:02,833
and never fold.

479
00:21:03,833 --> 00:21:05,083
But now...

480
00:21:06,125 --> 00:21:08,291
I'm glad you chose
Dachi High, Hinomaru.

481
00:21:08,375 --> 00:21:09,791
♪

482
00:21:09,875 --> 00:21:11,708
All right,
it's getting pretty late.

483
00:21:11,791 --> 00:21:13,666
We have a big day
tomorrow, guys.

484
00:21:13,750 --> 00:21:14,958
[HINOMARU]
Got it!

485
00:21:15,041 --> 00:21:16,708
We better get some sleep, too.

486
00:21:16,791 --> 00:21:18,625
[YUMA]
Kill the lights while you're up.

487
00:21:18,708 --> 00:21:19,916
[REINA]
Sure thing.

488
00:21:22,208 --> 00:21:23,500
I want to thank you all.

489
00:21:23,583 --> 00:21:25,000
[ALL]
Huh?

490
00:21:27,250 --> 00:21:29,541
He gonna tell us what for? Nope.

491
00:21:29,625 --> 00:21:30,541
Seriously.

492
00:21:31,708 --> 00:21:32,708
[switch clicks]

493
00:21:34,458 --> 00:21:37,416
Let's go out there
tomorrow and win!

494
00:21:38,416 --> 00:21:39,458
[ALL BOYS]
Yeah!

495
00:23:13,291 --> 00:23:15,166
This is the first time
we've hit the bath as a team!

496
00:23:15,250 --> 00:23:16,625
Totally butt naked!

497
00:23:16,708 --> 00:23:19,416
It's not like it's
that much different than usual.

498
00:23:19,500 --> 00:23:21,291
Aren't you getting in, Coach?

499
00:23:21,375 --> 00:23:23,625
[KIRIHITO] It's dangerous
for me to stay in too long.

500
00:23:25,000 --> 00:23:26,500
[CHIHIRO laughing]

501
00:23:26,583 --> 00:23:27,708
Kunisaki!

502
00:23:29,375 --> 00:23:30,916
Come back here!

503
00:23:31,000 --> 00:23:32,208
Aah!

504
00:23:32,291 --> 00:23:33,958
[YUMA]
Wait till I get my han...

505
00:23:34,041 --> 00:23:35,500
Uh...

506
00:23:35,583 --> 00:23:36,541
[ALL]
Uhh...

507
00:23:36,625 --> 00:23:37,625
Aahh!

